For evaluating the performance of gas/vapor sensors, there are a few critical parameters including component resistance, measure resistance, sensitivity, limit of detection, response time, recovery time, and selectivity. The definitions and formulas of these parameters are summarized in Table 1.Table 1
Summary of the definition and formula of sensor parameters

Parameter
Definition
Formula

Ra
Resistance value of the device, when put into the dry, clean atmosphere

Rg
Resistance value of the device, when put into gas to be detected

